Herminericus, one of the two Roman Consuls in the year 465, may be mentioned here as having had some possible influence upon the traditional account of the great Gothic King Ermanric of the fourth century. 5 This Herminericus was the son of Aspar, a Goth or Alan,

and survived Aspar, who was assasinated in 471, A. D. 6
